╭─ Assistant [MainThread@3433734] ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ Proposed fix summary:                                                                       │
│ - In unfold() for the unconditional predecessor case, schedule unfolding of operand selects │
│ after rewiring the PHI, and only schedule the true-side select (SIOp1) if it has exactly    │
│ one use and that use is the PHI we just rewired (SIUse). Always schedule the false-side     │
│ select (SIOp2) via the new PHI (NewPhi).                                                    │
│ - This avoids creating a conflicting new use for SIOp1 that breaks the deadness invariant   │
│ when unfolding select instructions, addressing the assertion crash.                         │
│                                                                                             │
│ Patch:                                                                                      │
│ - llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/DFAJumpThreading.cpp                                           │
│   - Move scheduling of operand selects to after updating SIUse’s incoming values.           │
│   - Guard scheduling of SIOp1 with hasOneUse() and user == SIUse.                           │
│   - Continue scheduling SIOp2 with NewPhi.                                                  │
│                                                                                             │
│ This conservative scheduling ensures the original select being unfolded becomes dead after  │
│ PHI rewiring and prevents the crash observed in the reproducer.                             │
